l) by creating a platform to crowd-source the information directly from people like you.  The site would let you compare what you are paying for various goods and services with what others in your area are paying.  And guess what, this idea WON the weekend.  And we were voted the “Crowd Favorite”.  So basically, we came together as a group of personal finance nerds and crushed a startup competition.  Not bad for two-day’s work.\r\n\r\nWe’re not sure exactly where this site is headed, but we think this topic is important and we are working hard to bring you an engaging site with relevant data and useful content.\r\n\r\nStay tuned. There will be more to come.  In the meantime, connect with us on Twitter, Facebook, or through our Contact link.  We would love to hear your feedback on the site, ideas you have for future blog posts, and what types of costs cause you the most heartburn.  See you back here soon!\r\n\r\n- The CrowdCost Team','Welcome to CrowdCost','','publish','open','open','','welcome-to-crowdcost','','','2015-02-20 03:54:22','2015-02-20 03:54:22','',0,'http://ec2-54-165-48-87.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=25',0,'post','',1),(26,1,'2015-02-20 03:48:27','2015-02-20 03:48:27','Hello and welcome to CrowdCost!  Whether you stumbled on us accidentally or came specifically to share in our displeasure with opaque pricing, we are glad to have you.  Since you likely don’t know who we are or what we are trying to accomplish, let’s bring you up to speed.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBack in November 2014, we all signed up for a weekend where we met a bunch of random people, pitched ideas, formed groups, and cranked out the basic framework of a business in less than 48 hours.  Sound fun?  It was.  But it was also an intense fire drill with a bunch of strangers in an awkward setting (shout out to all the introverts out there)!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOur idea for the weekend was to bring clarity to frustrating pricing data (we’re talking about you, cable bill) by creating a platform 